properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 3:21AM PST until January 14 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
...ADDITIONAL SNOW EXPECTED MONDAY THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...

.Another round of light to moderate snow accumulations is
expected Monday through Tuesday morning. Snow level elevations
will fluctuate considerably throughout the event, likely from
between 2000 to 3500 feet. Regardless, many local interior
highways will see snow accumulations in higher elevations,
including Highways 299, 3, and 36. An additional, much stronger
storm will also bring heavier snow to the region Wednesday and
Thursday.

* WHAT...Snow accumulations of 4 to 8 inches possible Monday
through early Tuesday.

* WHERE...Del Norte Interior County.

* WHEN...From 10 AM Monday to 10 AM Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult, particularly near
high elevation highway summits. The hazardous conditions could
impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels will fluctuate considerably
during this event, ranging from roughly 2500 to 3500 feet in
elevation. Lowest elevation snow is expected overnight Monday
and Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state of California can be
obtained by calling 1-800-GAS-ROAD.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 10 AM PST TUESDAY ABOVE 2500 FEET
